title.narrative: Jiangxi Shihutang Navigation and Hydropower Complex Project

description.narrative: The development objective (PDO) of the proposed project is to improve utilization of the Gan River for more reliable freight transport and for cleaner energy production through: (a) improving inland waterway transport capacity and service levels for primary and secondary industries in the Nanchang-Ganzhou corridor of the Gan River; and (b) generating renewable electricity to help meet rapidly growing demand for energy in the region.

condition.narrative: Construct and operate a transmission system, under arrangements and a time schedule, satisfactory to the Bank.
Ensure that all actions necessary or required to address all findings and recommendations made by the Dam Safety Panel from timetotime during Project implementation.
Monitor and evaluate the progress of the Project and furnish to the Bank Project Reports semi-annually.
Retain the Dam Safety Panel until the Panel is satisfied, after the filling up of the reservoir under the Shihutang Complex, withthe start-up of operation of said Complex.
The audited Financial Statements for each fiscal year of the Borrower shall be furnished to the Bank not later than six (6) monthsafter the end of such period.

comment.narrative: Due to the development of Xiajiang ship lock at downstream of shihutang ship lock along Gan River, the inland waterway transportwas temporally suspended in Gan River near shihutang project location. Xiajiang ship lock was completed at May 2014.The economicanalysis for the delayed shihutang ship lock operation will be included in ICR.
The end target of power generation in 2013 is 472 GWH. And the actual power generated in 2013 was around 270 GWH.
